* Mon Mar 16 2020 Liz Nemsick <lnemsick.simp@gmail.com> - 0.3.0
- Drop support for EL6
- Add support for EL8
- Noteworthy changes
  - simp_nfs::home_dir_server and simp_nfs::mount::home::nfs_server must
    now be an IP address in order to support firewalld.
  - Removed obsolete simp_nfs::create_home_dirs::strip_128_bit_ciphers
    that enabled a workaround for EL6.
  - Added the following optional parameters to simp_nfs::mount::home that
    allow the user to control the stunnel connection for the home mount:
    - simp_nfs::mount::home::stunnel
    - simp_nfs::mount::home::stunnel_nfsd_port
    - simp_nfs::mount::home::stunnel_socket_options
    - simp_nfs::mount::home::stunnel_verify
    - simp_nfs::mount::home::stunnel_wantedby
- Removed dead code in simp_nfs::mount::home that attempted to detect if
  the server was also the NFS server.
  * This code used a non-existent variable to set an unused variable.
  * If this logic was 'fixed', it would introduce a problem whereby a NFS
    server could not mount home directories from another NFS server.
- Removed unnecessary inheritance of simp_nfs by simp_nfs::export::home.
- Added checks for nfs::is_server and nfs::is_client in simp_nfs::export::home
  and simp_nfs::mount::home, respectively. The export and mount logic will not
  work otherwise.

* Wed Jul 03 2019 Trevor Vaughan <tvaughan@onyxpoint.com> - 0.2.0
- Documentation update
- Fix acceptance tests
  - Remove pinning of autofs package

* Fri Jun 28 2019 Brandon Riden <brandon.riden@onyxpoint.com> - 0.2.0
